%@CR:MSE10001@%%@4@%The Microsoft(R) Editor is the first full-screen editor to run under both%@EH@%
OS/2 systems and DOS (Versions 2.1 and above). You can use the editor to
write programs, modify text files, and, under OS/2, run language translators
and other utilities in the background.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE10002@%%@4@%The Microsoft Editor was specially developed as a programmer's editor. It%@EH@%
offers an unsurpassed ability to work efficiently with many different files
in different directories, to interact with the environment, and to undo or
redo a whole series of commands. As a programmer, you can work faster and
more efficiently by using some of these features:%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE10003@%  ş  %@AB@%Compile and link programs from within the editor%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     Improve your productivity. The Microsoft Editor is more than a text%@NL@%
     editor; it is a development environment. Develop programs more quickly%@NL@%
     by compiling from within the editor. If the compilation fails, view the%@NL@%
     errors, rewrite the program, and recompileÄÄall without leaving the%@NL@%
     editor.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş  %@AB@%Create new editing functions in C or assembly language%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     Extend the editor's power by writing new functions. If you know how to%@NL@%
     program in C or assembly language, you can quickly learn how to write%@NL@%
     new modules for the Microsoft Editor. These modules involve no%@NL@%
     preprocessing; they become part of the editor itself and therefore run%@NL@%
     as fast as standard editing commands.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş  %@AB@%Customize the editor to suit your needs%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     Control how the editor behaves. The editor uses a special%@NL@%
     initialization file, TOOLS.INI, in which you can easily specify your%@NL@%
     own preferences for function keystrokes, screen colors, tabs, margins,%@NL@%
     and many other kinds of editor behavior. You can even specify%@NL@%
     preferences specific to type of file so that as you move between .C and%@NL@%
     .FOR files, the editor alters its settings.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE10004@%%@4@%This manual is a substantial revision of the %@AI@%Microsoft%@AE@% %@AI@%Editor User's Guide%@AE@%%@EH@%
for Version 1.0 of the editor. This manual has an expanded index, more
examples, detailed instructions for configuring the editor, and complete
documentation for writing editing functions in C.%@NL@%
