%@NL@%
     %@AS@%(S^2)+%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53306@%%@4@%Precedence is left to right in cases where a single character is surrounded%@EH@%
by two operators. If there is any doubt about the precedence of operators,
use parentheses.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53400@%%@3@%%@AB@%5.3.4  M 1.0 Matching Method%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53401@%%@4@%The matching method you use is significant only when you use a%@EH@%
search-and-replace function. The term "matching method" refers to the
technique used to match repeated expressions. For example, does %@AS@%a*%@AE@% match as
few or as many characters as it can? The answer depends on the matching
method. There are two matching methods:%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53402@%%@AB@%Method                      Description%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
Minimal                     The minimal method matches as few characters as%@NL@%
                            possible in order to find a match. For example,%@NL@%
                            %@AS@%a+%@AE@% matches only the first character in %@AS@%aaaaaa%@AE@%.%@NL@%
                            However, %@AS@%ba+b%@AE@% matches the entire string%@NL@%
                            %@AS@%baaaaaab%@AE@%, since it is necessary to match every%@NL@%
                            occurrence of %@AS@%a%@AE@% in order to match both%@NL@%
                            occurrences of %@AS@%b%@AE@%.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
Maximal                     The maximal method always matches as many%@NL@%
                            characters as it can. For example, %@AS@%a#%@AE@% matches%@NL@%
                            the entire string %@AS@%aaaaaa%@AE@%.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53403@%%@4@%The significance of these two methods may not be apparent until you use%@EH@%
search and replace. For example, if %@AS@%a+%@AE@% (minimal matching plus) is the search
string and %@AS@%EE%@AE@% is the replacement string,%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     %@AS@%aaaaa%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53404@%%@4@%is replaced with%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     %@AS@%EEEEEEEEEE%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53405@%%@4@%because each occurrence of %@AS@%a%@AE@% is immediately replaced by %@AS@%EE%@AE@%. However, if %@AS@%a#%@AE@%%@EH@%
(maximal matching plus) is the search string, the same string is replaced
with%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     %@AS@%EE%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53406@%%@4@%because the entire string %@AS@%aaaaa%@AE@% is matched at once and replaced with %@AS@%EE%@AE@%.%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
