letter %@AB@%H%@AE@%. Each matching string is replaced by a new string that consists of
the original digits (which were tagged so they could be reused) and the
prefix %@AB@%16#%@AE@%. For example, the string %@AS@%1a000H%@AE@% is replaced with the string
%@AS@%16#1a000%@AE@%.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53605@%%@4@%The editor recognizes six special charactersÄÄ%@AB@%$  (  ,  )  -%@AE@%%@AB@%\%@AE@%ÄÄwithin%@EH@%
replacement strings. Each of these characters should be preceded by a
backslash (%@AB@%\%@AE@%) if you want to use a literal occurrence of one of them in a
replacement string. The %@AS@%#%@AE@% sign in the replacement string shown above is not
treated as a regular-expression character.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53606@%%@4@%You can also use the expression%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     %@AB@%$(%@AE@%%@AI@%w%@AE@%%@AB@%,%@AE@%%@AI@%n%@AE@%%@AB@%)%@AE@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53608@%%@4@%in which %@AI@%w%@AE@% is a field length. This number can be positive or negative. A%@EH@%
negative number indicates left justification.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53609@%%@4@%If %@AI@%w%@AE@% is greater than the length of the tagged expression, the editor right%@EH@%
justifies the tagged expression within the field and pads the field with
leading spaces. If %@AI@%w%@AE@% is greater than the length of the expression but is
preceded by a negative sign, the editor left justifies the expression and
pads the field with trailing spaces. If %@AI@%w%@AE@% is equal or less than the length
of the expression, the editor prints the whole expression but does not pad
with spaces.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53700@%%@3@%%@AB@%5.3.7  Predefined M 1.0 Regular Expressions%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE53701@%%@4@%Several M 1.0 regular expressions are defined in Table 5.1%@BO:   28999@% for your%@EH@%
convenience. You can use them by entering %@AB@%:%@AE@%%@AI@%letter%@AE@% in a regular expression.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSE5T100@%%@4@%%@AU@%Table 5.1  Predefined Expressions%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@TH:   25   1060  1 12 42 22 @%%@AB@%Letter      Meaning                                   Description%@AE@%%@AB@%:a%@AE@%          [a-zA-Z0-9]                               Alphanumeric%@AB@%:b%@AE@%          ([\t]#)                                   White space%@AB@%:c%@AE@%          [a-zA-Z]                                  Alphabetic%@AB@%:d%@AE@%          [0-9]                                     Digit%@AB@%:f%@AE@%          ([~"\[\]\:<|>+=;,.\\/]#)                  Portion of a file name%@AB@%:h%@AE@%          ([0-9a-fA-F]#)                            Hexadecimal number%@AB@%:i%@AE@%          ([a-zA-Z_$][a-zA-Z0-9_$]@)                C-language identifier%@AB@%:n%@AE@%          ([0-9]#[0-9]@![0-9]@.[0-9]#![0-9]#)       Number%@AB@%:p%@AE@%          (([a-z]\:!)(\\!)(:f(:f!)\\)@:f(.:f!))     Path%@AB@%:q%@AE@%          ("[~"]@"!'[~']@')                         Quoted string%@AB@%:w%@AE@%          ([a-zA-Z]#)                               Word%@AB@%:z%@AE@%          ([0-9]#)                                  Integer%@TE:   25   1060  1 12 42 22 @%
