%@CR:MSE9R026@%%@4@%The following example causes the editor to report an invalid-argument%@EH@%
message if the range of lines is greater than 10. Normally this condition is
not an error, but you may want to write a function that restricts the size
of an argument.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     if( yEnd > yStart == 10 )%@NL@%
     {%@NL@%
         BadArg( );%@NL@%
         return 0;%@NL@%
     }%@NL@%
