%@CR:MSEb0001@%%@4@%This appendix discusses two programs that work in conjunction with the%@EH@%
Microsoft Editor:%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb0002@%  ş  UNDEL.EXE%@NL@%
%@NL@%
  ş  EXP.EXE%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb0003@%%@4@%Both programs work with backup files. When a file is updated and the %@AB@%backup%@AE@%%@EH@%
switch is set to %@AB@%undel%@AE@%, the old version of the file is copied to a hidden
subdirectory called DELETED. UNDEL.EXE and EXP.EXE manipulate the files in
the DELETED subdirectory.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb1000@%%@2@%%@AB@%B.1  UNDEL.EXE%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb1001@%%@4@%Use this program to move a file from the DELETED subdirectory to the parent%@EH@%
directory. Its command-line syntax is as follows:%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     undel ®%@AI@%filename%@AE@%¯%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb1002@%%@4@%If %@AI@%filename%@AE@% is not given, the contents of the DELETED subdirectory are%@EH@%
listed. If there is more than one version of the file, you are given a list
to choose from. If the file already exists in the parent directory, the two
files are swapped.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb2000@%%@2@%%@AB@%B.2  EXP.EXE%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb2001@%%@4@%Use this program to remove all of the files in the hidden DELETED%@EH@%
subdirectory of the specified directory. Use the following command-line
syntax:%@NL@%
%@NL@%
     exp ®/r¯ ®/q¯ ®%@AI@%directory%@AE@%¯%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEb2002@%%@4@%If no %@AI@%directory%@AE@% is specified, the current directory's DELETED subdirectory%@EH@%
is used. If the /r option is given, EXP.EXE recursively operates on all
subdirectories. The /q option specifies quiet mode; the deleted file names
are not displayed on the screen.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
