%@CR:MSEc0001@%%@4@%This appendix lists the messages that the editor can report on the dialog%@EH@%
line, along with explanations. Some of these messages represent error
conditions; in that case, the explanation given describes what went wrong
and what action to take to correct the error. Other messages prompt you for
information or report what operation is taking place. For example, the
editor displays a message whenever it saves a file.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEc0002@%%@4@%The messages are listed in two sections. The first section consists of%@EH@%
messages that begin with a placeholder. A "placeholder" is a piece of
informationÄÄsuch as a number or a file nameÄÄthat varies with the
situation. This section is organized alphabetically by the placeholder type.
The second section consists of messages that do not begin with a
placeholder. These messages are organized alphabetically by first symbol or
word.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEc1000@%%@2@%%@AB@%C.1  Messages Starting with Placeholders%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE001@%%@4@%%@AI@%driveletter%@AE@%%@AB@% is an invalid drive%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You attempted to use %@AI@%Setfile%@AE@% to change the current drive to a%@NL@%
               drive not recognized by your system. Use a different drive%@NL@%
               letter.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE002@%%@4@%%@AI@%file%@AE@%%@AB@% does not exist%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You gave the %@AI@%Arg Arg filename Paste%@AE@% command, but the file%@NL@%
               specified does not exist. Make sure you give the complete%@NL@%
               path name of the file if it is not in the current directory.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE003@%%@4@%%@AI@%file%@AE@%%@AB@% does not exist. Create?%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               When you started the editor, you specified a file that does%@NL@%
               not exist. Type Y to create the file or N to avoid creating%@NL@%
               the file, in which case the editor loads the most recently%@NL@%
               edited file.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE004@%%@4@%%@AI@%file%@AE@%%@AB@% has been changed.  Refresh?%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               One of the files opened for editing was altered by a program%@NL@%
               other than the editor. This change has not yet been reflected%@NL@%
               in the file buffer. You should either type Y to discard%@NL@%
               recent edits and have the editor reread the file from disk,%@NL@%
               or type N to preserve your edits. If you answer N, you should%@NL@%
               execute a save operation so that the file buffer is copied to%@NL@%
               the file stored on disk.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE005@%%@4@%%@AI@%file%@AE@%%@AB@% has changed. Save changes (Y/N)?%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You have attempted to exit, and the file you are currently%@NL@%
               working on has been changed since it was last saved. If you%@NL@%
               respond Y, the changes will be saved; if N, they will be%@NL@%
               discarded.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE006@%%@4@%%@AI@%file%@AE@%%@AB@% is read-only%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You attempted to overwrite a file that has the read-only%@NL@%
               attribute. After displaying this message, the editor prompts%@NL@%
               for a new file name under which to save the file. If you%@NL@%
               assigned a command line to the %@AB@%readonly%@AE@% switch, the editor%@NL@%
               asks if you want to execute this command.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE007@%%@4@%%@AB@%'%@AE@%%@AI@%keystroke%@AE@%%@AB@%' is an unknown key%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You gave an unrecognized keystroke in an assignment. Some%@NL@%
               keyboards may support keystroke combinations that the editor%@NL@%
               does not accept.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE008@%%@4@%%@AI@%keystroke%@AE@%%@AB@% is not assigned to any editor function%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               The keystroke you pressed has no editing function assigned to%@NL@%
               it (not even the %@AI@%Graphic%@AE@% function, which makes keystrokes%@NL@%
               literal). You must assign a function to a keystroke before%@NL@%
               using it.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE009@%%@4@%%@AI@%name%@AE@%%@AB@% is not an editor function%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You attempted to assign an undefined function to a keystroke.%@NL@%
               You may have mistyped the function name, or you may have used%@NL@%
               the colon (:) instead of the definition symbol (:=) to enter%@NL@%
               a macro definition.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE010@%%@4@%%@AI@%name%@AE@%%@AB@% is not an editor switch%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You entered an assignment in which the left side did not%@NL@%
               contain a recognized function, macro, or switch name. You may%@NL@%
               have mistyped the name or used the wrong syntax.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE011@%%@4@%%@AI@%number%@AE@%%@AB@% occurrences found%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               The %@AI@%Searchall%@AE@% function found %@AI@%number%@AE@% occurrences of the search%@NL@%
               string.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE012@%%@4@%%@AI@%number%@AE@%%@AB@% occurrences replaced%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               The %@AI@%Replace%@AE@% or %@AI@%Qreplace%@AE@% function replaced %@AI@%number%@AE@% occurrences%@NL@%
               of the search string.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE013@%%@4@%%@AI@%number%@AE@%%@AB@%: Undefined opcode%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               The editor detected an internal error in the way it analyzed%@NL@%
               a regular expression. Please note the circumstances of this%@NL@%
               error and notify Microsoft Corporation by following the%@NL@%
               directions in the Microsoft Product Assistance Request form%@NL@%
               at the back of one of your manuals.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE014@%%@4@%%@AB@%+'%@AE@%%@AI@%string%@AE@%%@AB@%' not found%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               The %@AI@%Psearch%@AE@% function failed to find an occurrence of %@AI@%string%@AE@%.%@NL@%
               This message may be reported for both ordinary and%@NL@%
               regular-expression searches.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE015@%%@4@%%@AI@%value%@AE@%%@AB@% is an illegal setting%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You attempted to give an illegal value in a switch%@NL@%
               assignment.%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEc2000@%%@2@%%@AB@%C.2  Other Messages%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
%@CR:MSEcE016@%%@4@%%@AB@%<ZFormat???>%@AE@%%@EH@%%@NL@%
%@NL@%
               You used the percent sign (%@AS@%%%@AE@%) in a text switch (such as%@NL@%
